description:
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited from confident, motivated and energetic individuals to work in our Point of Care Testing (POCT) team that support over 150 devices across the Trust. Diagnostic tests are performed on the these devices and the team are responsible for ensuring accurate high quality results through quality control, training and support to the clinical teams that use them.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will involve working as part of the team to perform a range of tasks that contribute to the smooth running of the POCT devices including: system administration, reagent management, device maintenance, operator training and audits. The successful candidate will be able to develop excellent work relationships with the clinical team and colleagues in POCT team, work equally well with others as independently and have good problem solving skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
